{"TopicId":27563,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"How Is Delta V Calculated?","CreatedByName":"RazorWolf19","CreatedById":62293,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:21:52Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RazorWolf19","CreatedById":62293,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:21:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI would love to learn the formula for calculating Delta V, I can imagine it would be extremely useful for my interplanetary missions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESo, just a thought here, is it something to do with:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E -Amount of Fuel\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E -ISP\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E -Thrust from Engine\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd if those are the values, how do you work with them to get a m/s answer?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E Thanks in advance. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zzz","CreatedById":63211,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:25:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Advanced_Rocket_Design\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Tutorial:Advanced_Rocket_Design\u003C/a\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AviatOrme","CreatedById":51126,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:26:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWell, the shortest answer is to use the Tsiolkovsky rocket equation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat will give you the dV of a stage or rocket.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/6k29lej.png\u0022 alt=\u00226k29lej.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFor more details, Wikipedia is your friend!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsiolkovsky_rocket_equation\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsiolkovsky_rocket_equation\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RazorWolf19","CreatedById":62293,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:27:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThanks for quick replies!\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rryy","CreatedById":57357,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:28:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/w/images/math/0/4/8/0483f8c3776bea32f980636d13d3d7a1.png\u0022 alt=\u00220483f8c3776bea32f980636d13d3d7a1.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u00C3\u017D\u00E2\u20ACv is delta-v, and the m1 and m2 are full mass and dry mass.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"smarky55","CreatedById":17137,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:29:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/4/5/945a66bb8ac5a46fd959ab6c12eebb00.png\u0022 alt=\u0022945a66bb8ac5a46fd959ab6c12eebb00.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ewhere m0 is start mass(with propellant)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Em1 is final mass (after burning propellant)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eve is exhaust velocity which is ISP * 9.81\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eln is log base e (e = 2.718)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ethis is all from \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsiolkovsky_rocket_equation\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tsiolkovsky_rocket_equation\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEDIT:\u003C/strong\u003EWow triple ninja \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-05-19T15:32:12Z\u0022 title=\u002205/19/2013 03:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EMay 19, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by smarky55\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fractal_UK","CreatedById":61595,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-05-19T15:30:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou can calculate it with the Tsiolkovsky Rocket Equation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u00C3\u017D\u00E2\u20ACv = v\u003Csub\u003Ee\u003C/sub\u003E ln (m\u003Csub\u003E0\u003C/sub\u003E / m\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E) \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhere v\u003Csub\u003Ee\u003C/sub\u003E is the exhaust velocity (specific impulse*g), m\u003Csub\u003E0\u003C/sub\u003E is the initial mass of the rocket and m\u003Csub\u003E1\u003C/sub\u003E is the mass of the rocket after all fuel is expended.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}